<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="19">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName class="Leotiomycetes" family="Thelebolaceae" genus="Coprotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Coprotus sexdecimsporus" order="Thelebolales" pageId="4" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sexdecimsporus">Coprotus sexdecimsporus</taxonomicName>
(P. Crouan &amp; H. Crouan) Kimbr. &amp; Korf.
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="4" pageNumber="19">
As presently circumscribed, the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Leotiomycetes" family="Thelebolaceae" genus="Coprotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Coprotus" order="Thelebolales" pageId="4" pageNumber="19" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Coprotus</taxonomicName>
is clearly characterised by the following combination of characters: obligate coprophilous ecology, eugymnohymenial 
<pageBreakToken pageId="5" pageNumber="20" start="start">apothecial</pageBreakToken>
development, apothecia with reduced marginal tissue without setose hairs; inamyloid asci uniformly stainable in CR, with functional operculum; prolate, smooth (under transmission light microscope), eguttulate ascospores in all developmental stages sporoplasm of which have strong affinities to form de Bary bubble in any anhydrous conditions (especially in media such Cotton Blue). Mature spores ejected from living asci possess temporary thick and gelatinous sheath. Anamorph not known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
